qas.question: What was the name of the hotel located at the corner of Illinois Avenue and the boardwalk?
What year was The Traymore Hotel begun?
Who was the owner of The Traymore Hotel?
How many stories was The Traymore Hotel after its renovation?
What was the name of the firm commissioned to build The Traymore Hotel?

context: <a0_0>The Traymore Hotel<a0_0/> was located at the corner of Illinois Avenue and the boardwalk. Begun in <a1_0>1879<a1_0/> as a small boarding house, the hotel grew through a series of uncoordinated expansions. By 1914, the hotel's owner, <a2_0>Daniel White<a2_0/>, taking a hint from the Marlborough-Blenheim, commissioned the firm of <a4_0>Price and McLanahan<a4_0/> to build an even bigger hotel. Rising <a3_0>16<a3_0/> stories, the tan brick and gold-capped hotel would become one of the city's best-known landmarks. The hotel made use of ocean-facing hotel rooms by jutting its wings farther from the main portion of the hotel along Pacific Avenue.
